{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d4c03bc6-0357-4ffb-afbf-1db5b65d2670","content":"Here are the most common options depending on your stack:\n\n**ASP.NET Core (dotnet)**\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth Individual   # Identity + JWT\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg    # Microsoft Entra ID (Azure AD)\ndotnet new webapi --auth MultiOrg     # Multi-tenant Azure AD\ndotnet new webapi --auth Windows      # Windows/Negotiate auth\n```\n\n**Node.js/Express** — Use `express-generator` then add:\n- `passport` + `passport-jwt` for JWT\n- `passport-local` for username/password\n- `@azure/msal-node` for Azure AD\n\n**Python/FastAPI** — Use `fastapi` with:\n- `python-jose` for JWT\n- `authlib` for OAuth2/OIDC\n\n**Common auth patterns:**\n| Pattern | Best for |\n|---|---|\n| JWT Bearer tokens | SPAs, mobile, microservices |\n| OAuth2 / OIDC | Third-party login (Google, GitHub) |\n| API Keys | Simple service-to-service |\n| Cookie-based | Traditional server-rendered apps |\n\nWould you like me to scaffold a specific project? If so, let me know your preferred language/framework and auth type.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f9189e37-11a5-47f7-b6a8-b6081cbde183","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking a general knowledge question about web API project templates and authentication options. This doesn't require any tool calls - I can answer from my knowledge of common web frameworks.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer covering the most popular options.","outputTokens":360},"id":"a89044e3-1861-47f5-b6a7-1a3142218af9","timestamp":"2026-04-08T00:50:11.573Z","parentId":"a30d7d1d-409c-45ec-bda9-6764ef563f73"}
